<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-10-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="568" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 21558/3.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Vice and Deputy Consul General <persName type="from">Cauldwell</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Alexandria</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-10-02"><hi rend="italic">October 2,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Egyptian ministry for foreign affairs says it is unable to arrest Memar
                            Rizk, as he is a Syrian, but will arrest him on request of Turkish
                            Government. Meantime Rizk will be searched out and watched.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cauldwell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>